## Current Project State (snapshot)

Working prototype. Multi-crate Cargo workspace under `crates/`. SQLite + FTS5 storage,
sqlite-vec ANN search, catalog-driven provider selection, unified inference queue
(`InferenceQueue`), hybrid search pipeline, bulk graph access (`get_all_edges`,
`get_nodes_paginated`). Interactive RAG chat REPL (`cli_chat`). Native GPUI graph
canvas renders real graph data with pan/zoom and LOD. No active bugs.

UI crates in progress (see `feature_UI.md`):
- `u-forge-graph-view` — `GraphSnapshot` + `build_snapshot()`, force-directed layout (grid-cell bucketed O(N) repulsion), R-tree spatial index, viewport culling.
- `u-forge-ui-traits` — `DrawCommand` / `Viewport` / `generate_draw_commands()` rendering pipeline (culling, LOD, type-color). Framework-agnostic.
- `u-forge-ui-gpui` — GPUI 0.2.2 canvas app: loads `memory.json`, builds snapshot, renders with pan/zoom/LOD. Run: `cargo run -p u-forge-ui-gpui`.

Recent quality improvements:
- `load_model()` now accepts `already_loaded: &[String]` — if the model ID is in the slice the HTTP round-trip to `/api/v1/load` is skipped entirely. Callers extract these IDs from `catalog.loaded` (already fetched by `LemonadeServerCatalog::discover`). `ProviderFactory::build` threads this parameter through all capability branches. Both CLI demos extract the loaded-model list from the catalog and fire all provider builds concurrently via `futures::future::join_all` / `tokio::join!`, eliminating sequential load waits on warm servers.
- `embed_all_chunks` is now incremental — uses `get_unembedded_chunks` / `get_unembedded_chunks_hq` (LEFT JOIN on `chunks_vec`) instead of re-scanning all objects.
- Hybrid search diagnostic blocks demoted from `info!` to `debug!` — no more log spam in production; `RUST_LOG=u_forge_core::search=debug` reveals full pipeline state.
- `KnowledgeGraphStorage` now uses `parking_lot::Mutex` — all 24 `.lock().unwrap()` calls removed.
- `ObjectType` enum deleted from `types.rs` — it was dead code; `ObjectMetadata.object_type` is `String` throughout, and `ObjectBuilder` already embeds correct string literals.
- `WeightedEmbedDispatcher::worker_count()` removed — `InferenceQueue` exposes `embedding_worker_count()` for callers. `WeightedWorkerSlot::name` and `idle` fields annotated with intent comments (retained for future diagnostics).
- HTTP timeouts added to all Lemonade HTTP clients — `LemonadeHttpClient::new()` sets 30s request / 5s connect; lightweight discovery clients (`system_info`, `catalog`) use 5s / 2s. Prevents indefinite blocking when Lemonade Server hangs.
- Token estimation changed from `len / 4` to `len.div_ceil(3)` — conservative 3-char/token ratio better matches dense TTRPG prose. `split_text()` in `text.rs` uses the same ratio (`MAX_CHUNK_TOKENS * 3` chars per chunk).
- `EdgeType` collapsed from single-variant enum (`Custom(String)`) to transparent newtype struct. Use `EdgeType::new(s)` everywhere — `Custom(s)` no longer exists.
- `ObjectId` and `ChunkId` promoted from type aliases to newtype structs (`#[serde(transparent)]`). The compiler now rejects passing a `ChunkId` where an `ObjectId` is expected. Construct with `::new_v4()`; parse with `::parse_str(s)`.
- 9 clippy warnings resolved: `while let` loop, boxed large enum variant (`ProviderSlot::Tts`), `#[derive(Default)]` on `KokoroVoice`, transmute type annotation for sqlite-vec FFI, doc formatting. Edge metadata JSON parse failures now emit `debug!()` instead of silently swallowing errors.

The core library has been fully refactored (hardware abstraction layer removed):
- `hardware/` directory deleted — `NpuDevice`, `GpuDevice`, `CpuDevice`, `DeviceWorker`
  trait, and `HardwareBackend` enum no longer exist.
- `lemonade/device_factory.rs`, `lemonade/model_limits.rs`, `lemonade/registry.rs`,
  `lemonade/stack.rs` deleted. `LemonadeModelRegistry`, `ModelRole`, `LemonadeStack`,
  `EmbeddingManager`, and `TranscriptionManager` no longer exist.
- Replaced by: `lemonade/catalog.rs` (`LemonadeServerCatalog`), `lemonade/selector.rs`
  (`ModelSelector`, `SelectedModel`, `QualityTier`), `lemonade/duplicate_guard.rs`
  (`DuplicateGuard`), `lemonade/provider_factory.rs` (`ProviderFactory`, `Capability`,
  `BuiltProvider`).
- `ai/embeddings.rs` and `ai/transcription.rs` are trait-only files; implementations
  live in `lemonade/embedding.rs` and `lemonade/transcription.rs`.
- `InferenceQueueBuilder` now wires providers via `.with_provider(BuiltProvider)` /
  `.with_providers(Vec<BuiltProvider>)`. `ProviderFactory::build()` constructs them.
- `AppConfig` now includes `[chat]` section with per-device model overrides
  (`[chat.gpu]`, `[chat.npu]`). `ModelConfig.load_params` replaces the old
  `context_limits: HashMap`.

